## Day 7 - Linux Web Tools (curl and wget)

### Commands learned:
- curl -k https://site.com → fetch webpage
- curl -k -I https://site.com → see HTTP headers
- wget --no-check-certificate → download webpage

### What I discovered:
- College WiFi uses a proxy server
- Found proxy in HTTP headers: port 3128
- 403 Forbidden means proxy is blocking

### Security headers I found on github.com:
- Via: HTTPS/1.1 forward.http.proxy:3128
- Content-Type: text/html
- Connection: close

### Key learning:
- curl and wget are daily security tools
- HTTP headers reveal network architecture
- Finding a proxy server = real security skill
